# Walk Planner

For walking, use the Bezier gait planner instead of manual joint angles:

    walk = get_walk_planner(stride_length=0.10, swing_height=0.08)
    planner = walk['planner']
    period = walk['cycle_period']

    for i in range(n_steps):
        phi = (i * robot.dt / period) % 1.0
        robot.set_joints(walk_step(planner, phi))
        robot.step(robot.dt)

Parameters for get_walk_planner:
    stride_length: forward distance per cycle in meters (default 0.10, range 0.04–0.15)
    swing_height:  peak foot lift in meters (default 0.08, range 0.04–0.12)
    body_height:   body height in meters (default 0.27)
    cycle_period:  seconds per gait cycle (default 0.4, range 0.3–0.6)

walk_step(planner, phi) returns a 12-dim joint angle array for cycle phase phi ∈ [0, 1).
robot.dt is the simulation timestep — use it to advance phi each step.

To walk for a given distance, estimate steps: n_steps ≈ distance / (stride_length * robot.dt / cycle_period).
To walk for a given duration: n_steps = int(duration / robot.dt).

# Checkpoints

After completing each subtask, call robot.checkpoint("name") to record the robot's state:

    robot.set_joints(get_sit_pose())
    robot.step(2.0)
    robot.checkpoint("sit")

Checkpoint names must match the task names listed below. The system computes a reward at each checkpoint. You will see per-task rewards in the trial history.